.SH NAME

.B uriel
- Yet another static website generator

.SH SYNOPSIS

.B uriel
<project-root>

.SH DESCRIPTION

Uriel is a minimalistic, stable, feature complete static site generator,
written in Python.

https://nathanrosenquist.com/uriel/

.SH OVERVIEW

Uriel is designed to create static web sites, using a combination of content
nodes and HTML templates. The results are merged into a static web site, which
can be hosted pretty much anywhere.

This man page is not a comprehensive reference. It is intended to act more
like a cheat sheet, as an additional supplement to the full documentation.

.SH USAGE

\fBuriel\fP <project-root>

If the project root is a directory that does not exist, it will be created and
initialized with new project files. Subsequent invocations of the \fBuriel\fP
command against the project root will regenerate the static files of the web
site from the project files.

.SH HEADERS

Node files support headers. You can define and reference any custom headers
you want. Some headers also have special meanings, and are interpreted
directly by \fBuriel\fP.

Some special headers can be set on any node, while others will only take
effect if they are set on the root node (\fIindex\fP).

