.B Inheritance

The content nodes form a tree hierarchy, starting with the root node
(\fIindex\fP).
Generally speaking, if a header is set on a node, it will be inherited by
all downstream child nodes by default.

As an exception to this general rule, the following headers are specifically
not inherited:

.RS
.nf
.B Title
.B Created
.B Modified
.RE

To delete an inherited header from the current node:

.RS
.nf
.B -Foo: *
.RE

Set a header in child nodes, but not the current node:

.RS
.nf
.B +Foo: bar
.RE

.SH SUBSTITUTION PARAMETERS

Substitution parameters can be used in content nodes and HTML templates.

When a substitution parameter is encountered, it will be replaced with its
value during web site rendering.

